'''Fabiano Contarato''' (born in [[Nova Venécia]] on 20 June 1966) is a Law Professor, police chief, and a politician from Brazil affiliated to the [[Rede Sustentabilidade]] (REDE) party.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://especiais.gazetadopovo.com.br/eleicoes/2018/candidatos/es/senador/fabiano-contarato/|title=Fabiano Contarato 181 (REDE) Senador - Espírito Santo - Eleições 2018|website=especiais.gazetadopovo.com.br}}</ref> He was the most voted [[Federal Senate of Brazil|Senate]] candidate in [[Espírito Santo (estado)|Espírito Santo]] state during the [[2018 Brazilian general election]], with over one million votes — the first time he ran for an electoral post.<ref name="G1">{{cite web|url=https://g1.globo.com/es/espirito-santo/eleicoes/2018/noticia/2018/10/07/es-elege-fabiano-contarato-e-marcos-do-val-para-o-senado.ghtml|title=ES elege Fabiano Contarato e Marcos Do Val para o Senado|website=globo.com}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://veja.abril.com.br/politica/espirito-santo-fabiano-contarato-e-marcos-do-val-eleitos-para-o-senado/|title=Espírito Santo: Fabiano Contarato e Marcos do Val eleitos para o Senado|website=abril.com.br}}</ref> Contarato is the first out member of the LGBT community to be elected for the Brazilian Senate.<ref name=fir>{{Cite web |url=https://www.huffpostbrasil.com/2018/10/08/quem-e-fabiano-contarato-o-1o-senador-homossexual-que-tirou-o-lugar-de-magno-malta_a_23554408/ |title=Quem é Fabiano Contarato, o 1º senador homossexual que tirou o lugar de Magno Malta |website=HuffPost |author=Marcella Fernandes |date=7 October 2018 |accessdate=13 October 2018}}</ref> His win caused a seat loss for [[Magno Malta]], an Evangelical Pastor and ally of far-right Brazilian President elect [[Jair Bolsonaro]].<ref name=fir />

