A '''peace feeler''' is, in [[diplomacy]], a means of determining whether a warring party is prepared to end hostilities. [[William Safire]] defines it as "a diplomatic probe, real or imagined, to end hostilities."<ref>Safire's Political Dictionary, p. 528</ref>

